<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-685-157  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 685 157.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>The Wall Street Journal  Dec 17 1990 pB4(W) pB5(E) 10 col in.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Federal clearinghouse plans to track computer viruses; IBM, Lotuswill help. (National Institute of Standards and Technology)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Zachary, G. Pascal.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The National Institute of Standards and Technology (NIST) willestablish the first federal government effort to track and combatcomputer viruses.andP;  The virus clearinghouse has the support of IBMand Lotus Development Corp, with several other computer companiesconsidering offering their support.andP;  The clearinghouse will have aproposed budget of $1 million annually, too small a sum accordingto detractors of the plan.andP;  Critics of the concept say the NISTdoes not have the staffing or the funds to do an adequate jobmonitoring computer viruses.andP;  Proponents of the scheme say theNIST clearinghouse will create some much needed coherence at thenational level in the battle against viruses and computer crime.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     United States. National Institute of Standards and TechnologyComputer virusesGovernment AgencyData SecurityClearing HouseConsortia.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>